Description: [C:18059] Unable to perform bulk import Error: The MERGE statement conflicted with the FOREIGN KEY constraint "FK_SA_SPAA_Trustees_SiteCollectionId". The conflict occurred in database "StealthauditDB", table "dbo.SA_SPAA_Resources".
The statement has been terminated. Needs sent to R&D Eng for escalation

What We've Learned Updated: Identified issues with the SPAA Bulk Import job displaying the error below:

[C:18059] Unable to perform bulk import Error: The MERGE statement conflicted with the FOREIGN KEY constraint "FK_SA_SPAA_Trustees_SiteCollectionId". The conflict occurred in the database "StealthauditDB", table "dbo.SA_SPAA_Resources".

We have previously identified this error before on the 11.6 version of NEA and resolving this issue involved dropping all SPO tabels and re-running the SPAA System Scans and Bulk Import jobs again. Since then this issue has returned. 

We performed a FK validation check on both the SA_SPAA_Resources table and the SA_SPAA_Trustees tables using the dynamic management view command below:

use [database name]
dbcc checkconstraints (table_name);
go

This ran successfully and did not display any errors on both tables.

We collected all artifacts listed below:
SPAA Bulk Import Job Output folder
FK constraint error message txt file
msinfo32 dump file
process dumps of the SPAA Bulk Import job
Next Steps Updated: Once logs have been uploaded to the ticket an escalation to development will proceed

What We've Learned Updated: - Found a DLL error from our last HF patch on 1/30
--- It looks like instructions to resolve this were sent out 1/31 but no response.
--- We resolved this issue by unblocking all of the SharePoint DLLs in the PrivateAssemblies folder with the date of 01/30/2025 and then kicked off a new SPAC System Scan.

- Investigated the SP Bulk Import error (Foreign Key constraint) with development and found that the USN was much higher than the expected value. 
--- A fix for this is expected from development some time next week.

What We've Learned Updated: **SPAC Scan kicked off 3/3 is still running at 20hrs in. Previously, was failing at 24min.**

- Found a DLL error from our last HF patch on 1/30
--- It looks like instructions to resolve this were sent out 1/31 but no response.
--- We resolved this issue by unblocking all of the SharePoint DLLs in the PrivateAssemblies folder with the date of 01/30/2025 and then kicked off a new SPAC System Scan.

- Investigated the SP Bulk Import error (Foreign Key constraint) with development and found that the USN was much higher than the expected value. 
--- A fix for this is expected from development some time next week.

Steps to Reproduce Updated: 1. Run SPAA scan
2. Run SPAA Bulk Import
3. Get error
